This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on deep reinforcement learning and improving the learning speed of algorithms. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing an agent that can explore and learn from its environment. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is commonly used in robotics applications. The paper also mentions using deep learning for image processing, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the efficiency of learning could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
